  "text": "Lactating females increased their water input by 59.1% (this study) and energy intake by 35.2% [CITATION_1] compared with those of nonreproducing females when measurements were made on the same mice at the same time. This proportionally greater rate in water input than energy intake supported our initial hypothesis.",
